<center>
<h3>
About Robin Scagell</h3></center>

<center><img SRC="robin.jpg" height=350 width=375>
<br><i>Robin with a tiny glowing friend, 2001</i></center>

<p><a href="contact.htm">Robin Scagell</a> (born 1946 if you must know)
is a writer and broadcaster on astronomy (and occasionally glow worms)
who runs <a href="http://www.galaxypix.com">Galaxy Picture Library</a>,
which is devoted to photographs of astronomy and space.
<p>Robin’s background includes working at the Kodak Research Laboratory
as a research assistant, Manchester University as an observer and photographer,
and for the partwork publisher Marshall Cavendish as editor of magazines
on a wide variety of topics from photography and history to World War 2
and car maintenance. Since 1992 he has been running Galaxy Picture Library
and he pops up occasionally on Sky News and other stations, mostly talking
about astronomy and space.
<p>He is married to Sally who puts up with his astronomy and glow-worming
activities with much patience.
